    public interface Html5
extends HtmlBuilder
    Html5 builder.

    This interface contains html5 element types (e.g. Html5.DIV), and element builder methods (e.g. _div()).

    Element Type

    Each element type contains methods to set element-specific attributes, for example A.href(value).

    For common attributes or non-standard attributes, see methods in Html5.Element.

    If the element is a parent element, it has methods to add children, see Html5.ParentElement.

    Builder Method

    A builder method creates an element and adds it to the context parent, for example, _img().

    For each parent element, there are also two builder methods that take children, for example, _div(Object...) and _div(Runnable).

    Standard Conformance

    The elements and attributes conform to W3C HTML 5.1 draft.

    Relation to Html4

    Each Html5 element type is a subclass of the corresponding Html4 element type (if it exists in html4). For example,
    Html5.DIV extends Html4.DIV.

    Deprecation

    Three elements in html4, <acronym/big/tt>, are deprecated in html5; they don't exist in this interface as element types or builder methods.

    Many attributes in html4 are deprecated in html5; the corresponding methods are marked as deprecated, for example see Html5.A.name().
